---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Services"
  description="AI services, workshops, and implementation support for teams that want practical automation and clear next steps."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="ws-header">
      <h1>AI Services</h1>
      <p class="ws-desc">
        Strategy, workshops, and implementation support for businesses that want AI to improve real workflows, not just generate demos.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
      <div class="ws-worksheets-inline">
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Founders and owner-operators</strong>
          <p>Teams that need leverage quickly and want help turning repeated work into dependable systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Small teams with operational drag</strong>
          <p>Organizations dealing with fragmented handoffs, manual reporting, research bottlenecks, or content/process sprawl.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Leaders evaluating AI seriously</strong>
          <p>Teams that want an implementation path, constraints map, and a clear sense of what should be automated first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Core Offer Categories</h2>
      <div class="story-grid">
        <div class="story-card story-card-1">
          <h3>Discovery Workshops</h3>
          <p>Working sessions that map workflows, identify bottlenecks, score AI opportunities, and leave your team with a prioritized roadmap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="story-card story-card-2">
          <h3>Implementation Advisory</h3>
          <p>Architecture, tool selection, prompt/system design, and delivery guidance for internal AI systems and operational workflows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="story-card story-card-3">
          <h3>Build Support</h3>
          <p>Hands-on help turning the plan into something your team can run, measure, and extend without starting over every month.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Workshops and Engagements</h2>
      <div class="ws-worksheets-inline">
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Discovery Session</strong>
          <p>Best when you need clarity fast. We map current workflows, find the highest-leverage automation candidates, and define the next moves.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Automation Sprint</strong>
          <p>Best when the team already has momentum. We go deeper on process mapping, architecture, data flow, and what a buildable scope should include.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ws-worksheet">
          <strong>Implementation Engagement</strong>
          <p>Best when you need the system to move forward, not just the idea. I help shape the design, standing orders, operational model, and delivery path.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Typical Deliverables</h2>
      <div class="utility-grid">
        <div class="utility-item">
          <strong>Workflow map</strong>
          <p>Current-state workflows, bottlenecks, inputs/outputs, ownership, and the points where AI or automation can remove friction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="utility-item">
          <strong>Prioritized opportunity list</strong>
          <p>A ranked view of what to automate first, what to defer, and what should stay human for now.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="utility-item">
          <strong>Implementation blueprint</strong>
          <p>Recommended tooling, data flow, system boundaries, handoff design, review points, and rollout considerations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="utility-item">
          <strong>Working-session outputs</strong>
          <p>Decision notes, next actions, risk flags, and the artifacts needed to keep momentum after the session ends.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>How I Work</h2>
      <div class="jules-workflow">
        <div class="jules-workflow-item">
          <div class="jules-workflow-label">1</div>
          <div class="jules-workflow-content">
            <strong>Understand the operation.</strong>
            We start with the real workflow, not a generic AI use-case list.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="jules-workflow-item">
          <div class="jules-workflow-label">2</div>
          <div class="jules-workflow-content">
            <strong>Pick the right leverage point.</strong>
            We identify what is worth automating, what is risky, and what should stay manual.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="jules-workflow-item">
          <div class="jules-workflow-label">3</div>
          <div class="jules-workflow-content">
            <strong>Turn it into a buildable plan.</strong>
            You leave with concrete next steps, not a slide deck full of AI slogans.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clearer understanding of where AI will and will not help your team.</li>
        <li>Better operational design for research, reporting, content, and internal workflow coordination.</li>
        <li>A practical roadmap your team can execute without guessing at the implementation shape.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="jules-section">
      <h2>Start the Conversation</h2>
      <p>
        If you want help evaluating an AI workflow, shaping a delivery plan, or running a workshop with your team, reach out with the current problem and what you want to improve.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact/">Contact Jonathan &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
